📌 Frequently asked in UPSC.

---

# 🔴 Basic Structure Doctrine

Supreme Court stated:

👉 Parliament can amend Constitution,
BUT
👉 Cannot destroy its “Basic Structure”.

Developed in:

### **Kesavananda Bharati Case (1973)**

---

# 🔹 Elements of Basic Structure

Includes:

* Supremacy of Constitution
* Democracy
* Secularism
* Federalism
* Judicial Review
* Rule of Law
* Separation of Powers

📌 Not exactly defined fully.

---

# 🔹 Importance of Basic Structure Doctrine

Protects Constitution from:

* Misuse of amendment power
* Destruction of democracy

---

# 🔹 Difference Between Amendment & Ordinary Law

| Feature    | Constitutional Amendment | Ordinary Law               |
| ---------- | ------------------------ | -------------------------- |
| Article    | 368                      | Normal legislative process |
| Majority   | Special usually          | Simple                     |
| Importance | Constitutional change    | General law                |

